Selenium:
1.  Which framework you have used in your project?
        I have used Page Object Model(POM) with Pytest in my project

---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
2.  What is Hybrid framework
        It is a framework which combines two or more automation frameworks.
        It is a combination of multiple frameworks like Data driven + Modular + Method driven...
        It helps us in using the data from the external files

---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
3.  what is Xpath
        It is a locator which is used to locate the web-elements uniquely
        Using xpath we can locate any element on the application

---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
4.  what is // and / in Xpath
        /   --> Represents immediate child
                Used to write absolute xpath
        //  --> Represents any child
                Used to write relative xpath

---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
5.  which selenium version you are working
        Selenium 4

        To get the exact version, use the below syntax
            import selenium
            selenium.__version__

---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
6.  How do find the Xpath?
        Right click and inspect the web-element.
        The HTML code appears, depending on the data available, we write the xpath

---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
8.  What is Selenium Webdriver ?
        It will take the commands and sends them to browser.
        It supports many browsers. Eg : chrome, firefox, ie, edge,...

