9.  Have you used PyTest
        YES

---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
10. What are Fixtures ?
        A fixture is a reusable function in pytest which runs before and after the execution of the test_scripts
        It helps in avoiding the code repetition.

        The operations which executes before the execution of the test_scripts, we call them as setup
        The operations which executes after the execution of the test_scripts, we call them as teardown

        setup operation such as initialization of driver and launching of the web-application.
        teardown operation such as closing the browser

---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
11. how do you read data from excel
        Using xlrd
        STEP1   :   import xlrd
        STEP2   :   Open the excel workbook
                    workbook = xlrd.open_workbook()                     ## book object
        STEP3   :   Initialize the worksheet
                    worksheet = workbook.sheet_by_name("sheetname")     ## sheet object
        STEP4   :   Convert the sheet obj to the generator object
                    rows = worksheet.get_rows()                         ## generator obj
        STEP5   :   Traverse/typecast/next() to fetch the data from the gen obj

---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
12. How do you handle popups
        To handle the alerts, we will switch the driver to the alert

        SYNTAX  :   alert_obj = driver.switch_to.alert
                    alert_obj has two attributes to handle the alert
                    *   accept()    :   To accept the alert, we use this
                                        alert_obj.accept()
                    *   dismiss()   :   To dismiss the alert, we use this
                                        alert_obj.dismiss()

        To handle the browser notification pop-up
            from selenium import webdriver
            opts = webdriver.ChromeOptions()
            opts.add_experimental_option("detach", True)
            opts.add_argument("--disable-notifications")
            driver = webdriver.Chrome(opts)


            from selenium import webdriver
            opts = webdriver.FirefoxOptions()
            opts.set_preference("dom.webnotifications.enabled", False)
            opts.set_preference("dom.push.enabled", False)
            driver = webdriver.Firefox(opts)

