22. How to get the href of a link / get the source of image

        from selenium import webdriver
        driver = webdriver.Chrome()
        driver.get('')

        element = driver.find_element('loc_name', 'loc_value')
        element.get_attribute("href")       ## Gives the link
        element.get_attribute("src")        ## Gives source of the image

---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
23. Count the number of links in a page
        from selenium import webdriver
        driver = webdriver.Chrome()
        driver.get('')

        all_links = driver.find_elements('tag name', 'a')       ## list of web-elements
        print(len(all_links))

---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
24. How to check all checkboxes in a page
        *   Locate all the checkboxes on the page(using the common attribute)
            all_checkboxes = driver.find_elements("loc_name", "value")      ## list of web-elements
        *   Loop on the list and click on each checkbox
            for checkbox in all_checkboxes:
                checkbox.click()

