28. How do you launch IE/chrome browser?
        To launch IE
            from selenium import webdriver
            ie_driver = webdriver.Ie()

        To launch Chrome
            from selenium import webdriver
            c_driver = webdriver.Chrome()

---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
29. How to perform right click using WebDriver?
        Right click is a mouse operation. To perform mouse operations in selenium, we use ActionChains

        from selenium import webdriver
        from selenium.webdriver.common.action_chains import ActionChains

        driver = webdriver.Chrome()
        ac = ActionChains(driver)

        element = driver.find_element("loc_name", "value")
        ac.context_click(element).perform()

---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
30. How do perform drag and drop using WebDriver?
        Right click is a mouse operation. To perform mouse operations in selenium, we use ActionChains

        from selenium import webdriver
        from selenium.webdriver.common.action_chains import ActionChains

        driver = webdriver.Chrome()
        ac = ActionChains(driver)

        draggable_ele = driver.find_element("loc_name", "value")
        droppable_ele = driver.find_element("loc_name", "value")

        ac.drag_and_drop(draggable_ele, droppable_ele).perform()

---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
31. How to send ENTER/TAB keys in WebDriver?
        from selenium import webdriver
        from selenium.webdriver.common.action_chains import ActionChains
        from selenium.webdriver.common.keys import Keys

        driver = webdriver.Chrome()
        ac = ActionChains(driver)

        ac.send_keys(Keys.ENTER).perform()
        ac.send_keys(Keys.TAB).perform()

---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
32. How do you click on a menu item in a drop down menu?
        First we have to check whether the dropdown in standard or not
        If the tagname of the dropdown in "select", then it is a standard listbox

        If it is standard listbox, then we have to use Select class

        from selenium import webdriver
        from selenium.webdriver.support.select import Select

        driver = webdriver.Chrome()

        select_obj = Select(listbox_having_select_tag)

        Select has three attributes to select the elements from the dropdown
        *   select_by_index         :   select_obj.select_by_index(index_num)
        *   select_by_value         :   select_obj.select_by_value("value")
        *   select_by_visible_text  :   select_obj.select_by_visible_text("text")


        *   Suppose the dropdown is not standard, then we will locate the web-element amd will handle it

