42. What are the different exceptions you get when working with WebDriver?
        *   NoSuchElementException
                We get this when the element is not located(wrong xpath, element is not there in the web-page)
        *   ElementNotInteractableException
                When the element the still loading or it is not available to interact.
        *   TimeOutException
                When the condition in the expected_condition fails, we get TimeOutException
        *   ElementClickInterceptedException
                If the click operation in prevented/covered by some other element
        *   InvalidSelectorException
                When the CSS Selector and xpath syntax is wrong
        *   InvalidArgumentException
                When the operations performed on the web-element is invalid
        *   WebDriverException
                When the driver cannot interact with the browser
        *   SessionNotCreatedException
                When the browser version and driver verion mismatches
        *   NoSuchAlertException
                When we try to switch the driver to the alert but there is no alert
        *   NoSuchWindowException
                When we try to switch the driver to the window which doesnt exist or closed
        *   NoSuchFrameException
                When we try to switch the driver to the frame which doesnt exist


